HEADWORD: Bon vivant
<hw>Bon` vi`vant"</hw> <pr>(b⟦ocir⟧N` v⟦esl⟧`v⟦aum⟧N")</pr>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Bons vivants</plw> <pr>(-v⟦aum⟧N"z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[F. <ets>bon</ets> good + <ets>vivant</ets>, <pos>p. pr.</pos> of
<ets>vivre</ets> to live.]</ety> <def>A good fellow; a jovial companion;
a free liver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

